      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>Upper right corner of a <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> funerary <rs type="objectType">stele</rs> (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.43</measure> x
<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.47</measure>  × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.10</measure>) in the form of an <term lang="la">aedicula</term>, with simply moulded
gable and plain <term lang="grc-Latn">acroteria</term>, supported on columns with <rs type="decoration">Corinthian
capitals</rs>. Within the recess is the <rs type="decoration">bust</rs> of a <rs type="decoration">boy</rs> in relief.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p>ii is cut on either side of the bust and is presumably the
original inscription of the monument; i is cut in irregular lettering
on the gable.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p>i. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.01-0.02</measure>;
square <term>sigma</term> and cursive <term>omega</term>; ii. in standard second-
or third-century lettering, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.02-0.025</measure>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p>i. <date exact="none" cert="low" notBefore="0201" notAfter="0400">Third/fourth century</date> (<rs type="criteria">formulae</rs>, <rs type="criteria">penalty</rs>); ii.
<date notAfter="0300" exact="none" notBefore="0101">Second/third century</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>)</p>
      </div>

      <div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
